Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
deleteCellEdgeType(25.10)                            deleteCellEdgeType(25.10)

Name
       deleteCellEdgeType - Deletes the cell edge type constraint of the spec-
       ified cell

Syntax
       deleteCellEdgeType

       [-help]

       -cell <cellName>

       -edgeType <edgeType>

       Deletes the cell edge type constraint of the specified cell.

Parameters
       -cell <cellName>
              Specifies cell name to remove constraint.

       -edgeType <edgeType>
              Specifies the name of edge type to be removed.

       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes type and default in-
              formation for each deleteCellEdgeType parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command: man deleteCellEdgeType.

Related Information
              * report_cell_edge_type

              * specifyCellEdgeType

